250 inscriptions, mainly in Cyprus, some in the city of Ugarit
The Cypro-Minoan script was absent in some Bronze Age cities of Cyprus, yet abundant in others!
Unlike many other neighboring states, the Late Bronze Age collapse had only a slight impact on Bronze Age Cyprus
The Cyprot city of Enkomi even flourished, until 950 BC when the Cypro-Minoan script suddenly disappears, being soon substituted by the new Cypriot syllabary, whose inscriptions represent mainly the Greek language, with just a few short texts in Eteocypriot.  


